  "panels": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": 101,
      "gridPos": { "h": 3, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## API (Backend) Metrics — the RED method\nThese are **metrics** (numbers over time from Prometheus), not logs. They follow the **RED method**: **R**ate (how many requests/sec), **E**rrors (what fraction fail), **D**uration (how long they take). The top row is at-a-glance health — green is good, red means a threshold tied to an alert was crossed. Lower panels break those down over time and by route, plus .NET runtime health (GC, memory, CPU). For the log lines behind these numbers, open the **API (Backend) Logs** dashboard."
      }
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "alertmanager", "uid": "alertmanager" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 3 },
      "id": 100,
      "options": {
        "alertInstanceLabelFilter": "",
        "alertName": "",
        "dashboardAlerts": false,
        "groupBy": [],
        "groupMode": "default",
        "maxItems": 20,
        "sortOrder": 1,
        "stateFilter": { "firing": true, "pending": true, "noData": false, "normal": false, "error": true },
        "viewMode": "list"
      },
      "title": "Active alerts (Alertmanager)",
      "description": "Live alerts forwarded from Prometheus rule evaluation. Empty during normal operation. Each alert below corresponds to a threshold you'll see marked on the panels.",
      "type": "alertlist"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": { "mode": "thresholds" },
          "mappings": [],
          "thresholds": { "mode": "absolute", "steps": [ { "color": "green", "value": null }, { "color": "red", "value": 0 } ] },
          "unit": "reqps"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
